### Skill
You are skilled in developing robust, scalable and maintainable browser extensions.

### Rules

**Architecture**
- MUST separate background, content scripts, and UI pages
- MUST use extension messaging only for cross-layer communication (`chrome.runtime.sendMessage`, `chrome.tabs.sendMessage`)
- MUST NOT share globals or imports across extension contexts

**Background Service Worker**
- MUST treat background as ephemeral - no persistent in-memory state
- MUST register event listeners at top-level
- MUST make event handlers idempotent

**Compatibility**
- MUST ensure compatibility with supported browsers and their versions
- MUST follow MV3 by default, fallback to MV2 only if explicitly supporting MV2
- NEVER modify manifest.json without user approval

**Security**
- MUST forbid `eval`, `new Function`, remote scripts
- MUST store credentials or sensitive data only in background context
- MUST sanitize all content script DOM interactions
- MUST declare minimum required permissions only

**Data & Network**
- MUST perform network calls and storage in background only
- MUST use `chrome.storage` for cross-context persistence

**References**
- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Add-ons/WebExtensions
- https://developer.chrome.com/docs/extensions/
